What is block scope?
- Block scope means variable declared inside a specific block cannot be accessed from outside the block. defined by pair of curly backets {--}
eg - 
f (true) {
    let blockLet = "I am trapped inside!";
    const blockConst = "Me too!";
    console.log(blockLet); // Output: I am trapped inside!
}

// Attempting to access them outside the block throws an error
console.log(blockLet);   // ReferenceError: blockLet is not defined
console.log(blockConst); // ReferenceError: blockConst is not defined


What is Function scope?
- Block scope means variable declared inside a specific function cannot be accessed from outside the block. defined by pair of round backets (--)
eg - function localEnvironment() {
    var functionScopedVar = "I am trapped inside!";
    console.log(functionScopedVar); // Works fine
}

localEnvironment();

