What is Temporal Dead Zone?
-> Its the time period from start of the block scope until the js engine reaches the variable declaration statemenet. 
-> The variable exists in the memory but remains uninitiazlied so if we try to acces it before declare statmenet we will get reff err.

Why is const object mutable?
-> Object is compound data structure , the dont contain the actual data instead they stire the mmory refence, to avoid reasginement , so we can change the object declared with const but not a direct value,
-> const prevents reassignment of the variable, not modification of the object itself.
-> Objects are reference types. The variable stores a reference to the memory location where the object is stored, not the actual object.
eg -
const user = { name: "Alice", age: 25 };

// This is perfectly legal
user.age = 26; 
user.role = "Admin"; 

console.log(user); // { name: "Alice", age: 26, role: "Admin" }


