promise ->
- Promise is an object representing the eventual completion or failure of an asynchronous operation.
- promise has three states pending, fulfilled, rejected


eg -
const promise = new Promise((resolve, reject) => {

    let success = true;

    if (success)
        resolve("Success");
    else
        reject("Failure");

});

promise.then((result)=>{
console.log(result)
}).catch((err)=>{
console.log(err))};


Code execution ->
call stack -> micr staxck -> call back que



Call Stack -> 
 - The  call stack is data structure used by javascript to keep the track of function execution. 
- works on LIFO principle 

Call Back  ->
 - The call back is a function that passed as an argument to another function and xeuted later.

eg 
function greet(callback){
callback()
}

greet(() => {
    console.log("Hello");
});


Call Back Que ->
- als called as macro stack que.
- like settimeout , fetch are passed to this que. 
- it has lower priority than micro stack que

Micro Stack que ->
- has higher priority
- promises are passed to this que
- exxceutes before call back que

Event Loop ->
- Evenet is mechanism to continuely monitor call stack and when its empty first pass thentask from microstack and the from the call back quw to call stack






